main event: An oval-shaped object, the size of a propeller-driven aircraft, was observed on ground-radar at a distance of 7 to 10 miles, ranging from 15,000 to 18,000 feet in Clear Lake, South Dakota.
interesting points: The object was observed visually and through binoculars for an indeterminant period.
The object maintained a steady course with no maneuver.
The case was referred to Project Blue Book for further evaluation and comment.
Additional data will be indicated in monthly UFOB reports.
Photographs were taken of the object.
